Anno quarto Henrici octaui. These be the statutes established in diuers Parlyaments, for the mistery of the pewterers of London and concerning the search of pewter, brasse, and vntrue beames and weights, and for deceiuable hawkers, with diuers other orders and redresses to be had in the sayd mystery, with the renewing and confirming of the same statutes, Public General Acts. Selections: Pewterers. England and Wales. Wood, Thomas, fl. 1593. Mayor, William. Hyll, Walter.
[24] p.
[s.n.], [At London printed : Anno Domini. 1593]
Imprint from colophon. Signed: Thomas Wood Maister. William Mayor Walter Hyll Wardens. Signatures: A-C⁴. Reproduction of the original in the Bodleian Library.
